Corporate finance boutique DGP Advisory has appointed Andreas Grenacher (pictured) as managing director. He worked at German Investment Corporation DEG, in the Private Equity division before taking over as regional director and overseeing an investment portfolio of Sh600 million. &ldquo;East Africa, and Kenya in particular, has many exciting opportunities and we see a strong demand for an enhanced corporate finance offering,&rdquo; Andreas said. The corporate finance advisory firm operates across East Africa, and focuses on corporate and real estate, offering support in sourcing capital, both equity and debt for buyout or expansion projects. Andreas worked at Credit Suisse in a number of positions, including as head of structuring for Alternative Investments across Europe, Middle East and Africa. He also served as Vice President at Deutsche Bank&rsquo;s Investment Banking division .